## Backend (Spring Boot)
# bootRun uses profile `local`. Default: real Postgres (embedded off) — use Docker on 127.0.0.1:5432 or Supabase via SPRING_DATASOURCE_* below.
# Ephemeral DB only if you set LISTMYNEST_EMBEDDED_POSTGRES=true in this file (data lost when JVM exits).
# Optional: cd listmynest-backend/listmynest-backend && docker compose up -d
# bootRun loads, in order: ListMyNest/.env then listmynest-backend/listmynest-backend/.env (later file wins on duplicate keys; see build.gradle).
# Supabase: set SPRING_DATASOURCE_URL / USERNAME / PASSWORD (Session pooler JDBC from dashboard). Never put the password inside the JDBC URL.
# If something else uses 8080: SERVER_PORT=8081
SERVER_PORT=
# DB (required for Supabase / any non-default Postgres):
SPRING_DATASOURCE_URL=
SPRING_DATASOURCE_USERNAME=
# Password always as its own line (never inside the JDBC URL — @ breaks parsing).
SPRING_DATASOURCE_PASSWORD=
# Supabase: if db.<ref>.supabase.co:5432 times out, use Session pooler — copy host, port, and username exactly from Dashboard → Connect → Session pooler (do not guess the aws-0-<region> host; wrong region → "Tenant or user not found").
# JDBC form: jdbc:postgresql://<host-from-dashboard>:5432/postgres?sslmode=require
# Username is often postgres.<project_ref> for the pooler, not plain postgres.
# Transaction pooler (6543): add &prepareThreshold=0 to the JDBC URL for Hibernate/Flyway compatibility.
# Firebase Admin SDK: paste the full service-account JSON as ONE line, or leave empty / {} to skip Firebase (local bootRun).
# Do not put PowerShell here — Gradle loads this file as plain KEY=value text.
FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON=

